description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an inspiring and independent leader?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to leading the ward team to provide the highest standard of nursing care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a band 7 Ward Manager on Hebog Ward at Ysbyty Gwynedd Hospital which specialises in renal patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will ensure the day to day operational management of the ward and be instrumental in driving the quality improvement programme on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have significant experience in acute medicine and the designated speciality of renal. You will need to demonstrate an understanding of the benefits of a multidisciplinary approach to patient care and the ability to communicate with all professional groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging role requiring an exceptional candidate and in return you will be supported by the leadership team to develop your full potential for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits and a discussion is welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 16 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elinor Thomas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medical Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;elinor.thomas2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
